# Shopify API scopes (comma-separated list of permissions required for HotDash)
# 
# Core Dashboard Tiles:
# - read_orders: Sales Pulse tile, order tracking
# - read_products: Inventory Watch tile, product catalog
# - read_inventory: Inventory levels and alerts
# - read_locations: Multi-location inventory tracking
# - read_fulfillments: Fulfillment status tile
# 
# Optional Features:
# - write_products: Product management (if needed)
# - write_orders: Order modifications (for agent actions)
# - read_customers: Customer lookup and history
# - read_analytics: Additional analytics (beyond GA)
# 
# Agent SDK Requirements (if using customer support automation):
# - read_assigned_fulfillment_orders: Fulfillment tracking
# - read_merchant_managed_fulfillment_orders: Order fulfillment
# 
# Minimum required scopes for basic dashboard:
# read_orders,read_products,read_inventory,read_locations
# 
# Recommended scopes for full functionality:
# read_orders,read_products,read_inventory,read_locations,read_customers,read_assigned_fulfillment_orders,read_merchant_managed_fulfillment_orders
# 
# See: https://shopify.dev/docs/api/usage/access-scopes
SCOPES=read_orders,read_products,read_inventory,read_locations

